  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Accounts Manager / Accounts Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide management over a portfolio of clients to ensure required filings and submissions to be done by stipulated timeline</li>\n  <li>Scheduling, monitor, control, coach, train and develop team members including reviewing of tax computations, GST computations, accounting treatment and preparation of unaudited financial statements in compliance with relevant governing law</li>\n  <li>Work with external auditors, resolving any accounting or tax related issues for portfolio of clients</li>\n  <li>Develop and inspire a motivated team to be client-centric with competent people skills to engage with clients, response to clients in timely and efficient manner</li>\n  <li>Hands on and lead by example</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Recognised Degree in Accountancy or equivalent professional qualification (ACCA, CPA, CA etc.)</li>\n  <li>Tax Accreditation from SCTP (preferred)</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years relevant experience in outsource accounting work</li>\n  <li>Analytical with good inter-personal skills</li>\n  <li>Good understanding of corporate governance, regulatory compliance and accounting principles</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5 days work week with flexi-benefits</li>\n  <li>Growing company means you do not feel stagnant</li>\n</ul>",
